e_cloud/grpc_gcp/Grpc_gcpTest.java`\n\nWhat changed:\n- Added coverage for `GcpMultiEndpointChannel`, which was not previously tested.\n- New test verifies:\n  - Default multi-endpoint authority selection.\n  - Named multi-endpoint authority selection via `authorityFor`.\n  - Fallback to default when an unknown multi-endpoint name is requested.\n  - Routing through `GcpMultiEndpointChannel.ME_KEY` call option.\n  - Routing through `GcpMultiEndpointChannel.ME_CONTEXT_KEY` context.\n  - Call option precedence over context.\n  - Non-current backup endpoint is not used.\n- Updated the existing test channel builder helper to optionally record created channels while preserving existing behavior.\n\nI did not run tests, per instruction.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_05f0d39f67b865ca0169f8966119f88191a2ea11ec7d6fca72\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1705, "output": 704, "cacheRead": 82432, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 84841, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1777899095379, "responseId": "resp_05f0d39f67b865ca0169f896580340819186a99b2a2fd237d7"}, "toolResults": []}
